I wrote this poem 10years ago, back in school !
And finally got the chance to deliver it on a grand podium.... This time it was at #ToastmastersLeadershipConclave ! 

Thanks Toastmasters International for giving me this opportunity ❤️

POEM TITLE : Bubble Happiness

V.C.: @lookwhathemademedo ✅

P.S.: This is just half of the poem

"What is this fatty gonna dance?"

Many girls/women with bigger bodies fear to come on stage! The fright is common. Because why? - "What will people think?" "Hippo, Stage will break" and all those nonsensical body shaming comments coming towards them from the society.

This is your time LADIES!
COME UP! And dance your heart out!

I DID IT. I WILL DO IT AGAIN. You do it too?

My special performance on @__shadesofady__ 's Sangeet night ❤️

#BreakingStereotypes 
#bodypositivity

latestPosts.caption:
Happy World Mental Health Day to everybody! 
I’m excited to share that today, on this special day I was felicitated as one of the “Inspiring Personalities” who can bring change in the society.
Growing up I knew, how I struggled with my anxiety issues, panic attacks, body image issues and depression.
All my life I was shamed for my body weight. Nobody ever called me beautiful, but just CUTE! I received backlash from my relatives, so called friends and everyone around me. I had a long battle with society accepting me as NORMAL 😌 And again when I prove my worth to everyone who bullied me - YES, I CAN INSPIRE TOO! 
Today when I was given this honour, I said one thing “আমি সাধারণ মানুষের প্রতিনিধিত্ব করি” 

I am the influencer for ordinary.
I am the influencer for the people suffering from body image issues. 
I am the influencer who talks about body acceptance.
I am the influencer who wants to show how I carry myself in every sphere of my life, and how OKAY it is to exist as a “FAT” Person.
Also, I am the influencer who doesn’t promote obesity!

I don’t know how will I look like in future - Maybe slim? Or bulkier? Or dark? Or old? Face full of acne? Saggy skin folds? It can be anything but I have to accept myself the way I am. I promote body acceptance✅ 

When you stop accepting yourself the way you are, you start looking for other people’s validation, and negative comments bother you. 

I know, I am not a perfect human being, and so is everybody. But it is FINE! My feelings matter, I have emotions, I breakdown, I cry howl, I feel bad too.And when we all are imperfect in our own ways, and can have our own psychological issues WHY NOT SEEK HELP when needed? There is NO SHAME about it !

This World Mental Health Day, let us take a pledge to spread awareness, positivity and help! 

Because your mental health is PRIORITY ! 💕✅

Thanks to Sradhanjali Dasgupta for inviting & honouring me 🙏🏻 More power to you 💕

📸: Subhadra S Chakraborty 💕🧿😘

Si Nonna’s Brings Authentic Sourdough Neapolitan Pizzas to More Corners of Bangalore

Si Nonna’s, India’s foremost destination for authentic sourdough Neapolitan pizzas, is expanding its footprint in Bangalore with the launch of two new outlets—Indiranagar and Sumadhura, Hope Farm Junction. Known for its uncompromising commitment to traditional Italian techniques and premium ingredients, the brand continues to redefine the pizza experience for Bangalore’s ever-curious foodies.

At the core of Si Nonna’s is its signature sourdough pizza, made with a 24-hour fermented dough that delivers an airy and flavorful crust—true to Neapolitan roots. Inspired by a serendipitous discovery of Nonna Galliano’s original mother-dough recipe in Naples, this time-honored method is what gives Si Nonna’s its soul.

The menu featured a wide range of vegetarian, vegan, chicken, and pork pizzas that speak to the city’s diverse preferences.

Popular additions include the refreshing coolers, indulgent desserts like Nonna’s Tiramisu, and the much-loved Sicilian pistachio gelato. For those on the go, Si Nonna’s also offers quick bites like the signature Panuozzo and artisanal coffee.

Beyond the food, Si Nonna’s offers an immersive dining experience with open kitchens that showcase the art of pizza-making in real-time. Guests of all ages can engage with the brand through “make-your-own-pizza” activities, while the thoughtfully designed spaces serve as community hubs for birthday celebrations, pizza-making workshops, and more.

Experience Si Nonna’s—where every slice tells a story of Naples. Now 6 outlets across Marks Square, JP Nagar, Koramangala, Utopia, Indiranagar, Sumadhura

Weekend breakfast at Tall Oaks Kitchen & Bar in Whitefield, Bangalore! @talloaksbangalore 

Tucked away in a lush, nature-inspired setting, this hidden gem offers a resort-like dining experience right in the heart of East Bangalore. Their weekend breakfast, available from 8 AM to 11 AM, is an absolute must-try! 🍳🥓 From perfectly done eggs and hearty toast to refreshing salads and rich coffee, every bite is a celebration of flavor and freshness. 🥗🧡

Whether you’re planning a romantic breakfast date, a pet-friendly outing, or a family brunch under the trees, Tall Oaks has you covered with its open-air seating, ambient lighting, and Instagram-worthy vibe. 🌞📸

I love how they’ve kept their multi-cuisine excellence, top-tier service, and tranquil vibe consistent — even a year after their opening!

Trust me, you’ll want to bookmark this spot for your next Bangalore breakfast outing. 🌳
Book your table now: ☎️ 7975305837 / 7975305194
